<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4cce19ee-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s10561"><num value="10561">§ 10561.</num><heading> Grant authorization</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Attorney General shall award grants to States and units of local government in accordance with this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id4cce19ef-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/351/tI/s2801">Pub. L. 90–351, title I, § 2801</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/106/561/s2/c/1">Pub. L. 106–561, § 2(c)(1)</ref>, <date date="2000-12-21">Dec. 21, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/2788">114 Stat. 2788</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/107/273/dB/tV/s5001/b/1">Pub. L. 107–273, div. B, title V, § 5001(b)(1)</ref>, <date date="2002-11-02">Nov. 2, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1813">116 Stat. 1813</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id4cce19f0-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id4cce19f1-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id4cce19f2-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s3797j">section 3797j of Title 42</ref>, The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id4cce19f3-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2002—<ref href="/us/pl/107/273">Pub. L. 107–273</ref> inserted “and units of local government” after “States”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
